# Fintech Design Intelligence

Every design decision must support one of three feelings:
- Trust — my money is safe / this company is legitimate
- Clarity — I understand this product
- Control — I can manage my account easily

If a section does not support one of those three it should not exist.

## Layout
- Hero: left column headline + CTA, right column product UI or photo
- Page structure: Hero → Features → Benefits → How It Works →
  Trust Signals → FAQ → Final CTA
- One primary CTA per page
- Product UI or real people must appear every 2-3 sections

## Spacing
- Hero padding: 120px top/bottom
- Sections: 80px top/bottom
- Cards: 40px padding
- White space creates calm. Calm creates trust.

## Typography
- H1: 36-48px — one per page
- H2: 28-32px — section headings
- Body: minimum 16px
- Fonts: Outfit (headings) · Inter Tight (body)

## Trust Signals — every page needs at least 3
- Compliance language (payment facilitator disclaimer)
- Social proof — merchant count, reviews, ratings
- Security language — encryption, fraud monitoring
- Product transparency — fees, how it works
- Real product screenshots or real people photos

## Images
- Must demonstrate product usage or show real merchants
- No generic decorative stock photos
- Decorative images: alt="" aria-hidden="true"

## WCAG 2.1 AA
- Color contrast minimum 4.5:1
- Keyboard navigation on all interactive elements
- Labels on all form inputs
- Descriptive alt text on meaningful images
- Visible focus states: outline: 3px solid #9edd05
